# 19_toolbar_stragglers — substrate-layer suite for Toolbar.cpp's two
# value-held SpinButton members (s198 m1).
#
# Substrate-style test (per TESTING.md grandfather clause). Each
# sub-test proves the substrate contract holds — abbrev resolves,
# verbs dispatch, queries read back.
#
# Scope (s198 m1): the two SpinButton members that were value-held
# (Gtk::SpinButton zoom_spin / width_spin) and got flipped to
# pointer-held substrate (curvz::widgets::SpinButton*). Same
# architectural pattern as s196 m3's Bold/Italic CheckButton flip.
# Both live in popovers that are built eagerly inside
# Toolbar::Impl::build(), so their abbrevs are registered at app
# launch — no popover open required to address them.
#
# The flip proves the value→pointer pattern for SpinButton +
# Adjustment via the s189 m2 Adjustment-taking ctor. The pre-built
# Adjustment (zoom_adj / width_adj) is created at popover-build
# time, then handed to the substrate ctor along with climb_rate +
# digits. Existing application code that reads adj->signal_value_
# changed continues to work — the substrate's canonical signal
# (signal_value_changed on the spin itself) is independent of the
# adjustment's signal, both fire on a script-driven `set`.
#
# DSL note (carried from s196 m1): the DSL lexer is kind-strict.
# SpinButton `value` queries return Double. Round-number literals
# in asserts against numeric queries must be written with explicit
# `.0` suffix (`assert ... value == 0.0`, not `== 0`).
#
# The tested abbrevs:
#
#   Zoom popover    pop_tb_zom_spn   (zoom percentage SpinButton,
#                                     range 1..9500, digits 0)
#
#   Stroke popover  pop_tb_strk_w    (stroke width SpinButton,
#                                     range 0..9999, digits 1
#                                     at launch — refresh_stroke_
#                                     popover shifts to 2 / 3 when
#                                     display mode changes)
#
# Test protocol:
#   1. Open the Scripter window.
#   2. Load this script.
#   3. Run. Every line should PASS.
#
# Side effects: both SpinButton values are written to test the
# set/value round-trip. Zoom is restored to 100% at the end (a
# fixed, predictable end state — see the note below on why there's
# no environment-independent "launch default" to restore to). The
# width_adj signal is wired to emit_defaults() which pushes
# def_stroke.width; the test transiently moves it and restores 0.0
# (which is StrokeStyle's real type-level default).
#
# Note on zoom's launch value: zoom_adj is constructed with 100.0
# as its initial value, but by the time scripts can run, the canvas
# has loaded a document and Toolbar::Impl::set_zoom() has been
# called via MainWindow's fit-to-window flow, which writes whatever
# zoom level the document/viewport geometry produces back into
# zoom_adj. So there is no environment-independent "launch default"
# to assert against — the value on first script-read depends on the
# document size and the window size. Pre-DSL-variable-capture
# (banked from s195), we can't capture-and-restore at script time;
# the test settles for asserting the round-trip and leaving zoom at
# a predictable 100% end state.

#[sub] Zoom SpinButton — min/max document the adjustment range.

assert pop_tb_zom_spn min == 1.0
assert pop_tb_zom_spn max == 9500.0

#[sub] Zoom SpinButton — set/value round-trip.

pop_tb_zom_spn set 250.0
assert pop_tb_zom_spn value == 250.0
pop_tb_zom_spn set 50.0
assert pop_tb_zom_spn value == 50.0

#[sub] Zoom SpinButton — leave at a predictable end state (100%).

pop_tb_zom_spn set 100.0
assert pop_tb_zom_spn value == 100.0

#[sub] Width SpinButton — launch default is 0.0 (matches StrokeStyle default).

assert pop_tb_strk_w value == 0.0

#[sub] Width SpinButton — min/max document the adjustment range.

assert pop_tb_strk_w min == 0.0
assert pop_tb_strk_w max == 9999.0

#[sub] Width SpinButton — set/value round-trip.

pop_tb_strk_w set 2.5
assert pop_tb_strk_w value == 2.5
pop_tb_strk_w set 12.0
assert pop_tb_strk_w value == 12.0

#[sub] Width SpinButton — restore launch default.

pop_tb_strk_w set 0.0
assert pop_tb_strk_w value == 0.0

#[sub] Done. 2 new substrate widgets, both addressable. Toolbar.cpp
#[sub] is now at zero raw widget sites AND zero value-held
#[sub] SpinButton stragglers — fully migrated to the substrate.
